'''撒拉斐爾''' ([[希伯來語|希伯來語]]：{{Hebrew|'''שאלתיאל'''}}，[[英語|英語]]：{{lang|en|'''Selaphiel'''}} 或 {{lang|en|'''Selatiel'''}}、{{lang|en|'''Sealtiel'''}}；東正教譯'''撒拉斐伊爾'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.crkvenikalendar.com/datumcn-2015-11-21 |title=+++ 紀念天軍之統帥彌哈伊爾總領天使及其餘天軍神將 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2015-11-21 |website=crkvenikalendar.com |access-date=2019-05-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212193343/https://www.crkvenikalendar.com/datumcn-2015-11-21 |archive-date=2017-12-12 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>)，名字意為「向神祈禱」或「神之禱告」，是[[正教會|東正教會]]和{{tsl|en|Folk Catholicism|民間天主教}}傳統中的七大[[天使長|天使長]]之一。<ref>{{cite web |author=Yuri V. Konyev |url=http://www.3saints.com/angels.html |title=Names and Ranks of Angels |publisher=3saints.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120206021929/http://www.3saints.com/angels.html |archivedate=2012-02-06 }}</ref>

== 形像 ==
祂在[[聖像畫|聖像]]中被描繪為一位雙目低垂，雙臂交叉於胸前，正在虔誠[[禱告|祈禱]]的天使形像。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.holy-transfiguration.org/library_en/ang_heavhost.html |title=The heavenly host and our modern life |publisher=Holy-transfiguration.org |date= |accessdate=2011-12-05 |archive-date=2019-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827125831/http://www.holy-transfiguration.org/library_en/ang_heavhost.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>祂有時也被描繪為以下跪之姿祈禱，祈禱被認為是祂的特性。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.holy-transfiguration.org/library_en/ang_powers.html |title=The rational heavenly powers |publisher=Holy-transfiguration.org |date= |accessdate=2011-12-05 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111170210/http://www.holy-transfiguration.org/library_en/ang_powers.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[香爐_(基督教)|提爐]]是祂的另一象徵標誌。

== 聖經文獻 ==

== 主保 ==
在[[正教會|東正教]]和某些[[天主教|天主教]]傳統中，撒拉斐爾通常被看作是[[禱告|祈禱]]和團體服侍的[[主保聖人|守護聖者]]。

== 禱文 ==
在[[正教會|東正教]]和{{tsl|en|Folk Catholicism|民間天主教}}傳統中經常被誦唸的一篇聖撒拉斐爾代禱禱文：

{{lang|en|O Pure and Holy Archangel St. Selaphiel, you bow before the Almighty Lord offerinng angelic salutations of praise and thanksgiving. Guide us in our prayer. Like you, we would like to unceasingly pray and worship God the right way. May our lives be like incense pleasing to God. While awaiting for the inevitable time of separation from this material world, may we praise the Holy Trinity in the spirit of true love and humility throughout the days of our lives in eternity. Obtain for us these favors (name them) and present to God the Father all these petitions through Jesus Christ our Lord together with the Holy Spirit forever and ever. Amen.}}

